{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"934c7635-d060-40e1-9beb-a767b70629e1","content":"There's no pipeline in this repo, so here's a general guide.\n\n### Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) doesn't use `vstest.console`; it runs via `dotnet test`. Replace:\n\n```yaml\n# ❌ Old — VSTest runner\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblies: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\nwith:\n\n```yaml\n# ✅ New — Microsoft.Testing.Platform via dotnet test\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"\n```\n\n### Publish results & coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish TRX results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest   # TRX format\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key changes to your `.csproj`\n\nEnsure each test project opts into MTP:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Summary\n\n| Concern | Old (VSTest@3) | New (MTP) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console` | `dotnet test` / in-process |\n| Task | `VSTest@3` | `DotNetCoreCLI@2` |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` |\n| Coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Publish results | Automatic | `PublishTestResults@2` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"38f24854-4534-4cf3-a780-72d0eb56f86f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository is empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":679,"requestId":"3432:187D22:7185AFE:7DDE145:69F3FAD4"},"id":"0d473f91-2025-4365-b12f-4fd43c993901","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:59:12.285Z","parentId":"c1a7b1a2-3021-478d-beb4-284a928e4de9"}
